### 👤 User

I want you to do the following: Currently my neovim config is located at ~/nvim, it uses the standard LUA with lazy.nvim package manager, I want to create a nixvim flake here at ~/nixvim, that implements all the same functionality: plugins, keybinds, autocmds, options, etc that my neovim config uses. The docs are here: https://nix-community.github.io/nixvim/ or if you need source code for docs here: https://github.com/nix-community/nixvim/tree/main/docs https://github.com/nix-community/nixvim/blob/main/templates/simple/flake.nix here is example of how to create the standalone flake.nix for nixvim, config/ folder will contain all the plugins and options and autocmds. Plugins by name are here https://github.com/nix-community/nixvim/tree/main/plugins/by-name, if there isn't a plugin that we need from nixvim, then you should check nixpkgs and implement like so: - Register the plugin through extraPlugins: extraPlugins = [pkgs.vimPlugins."\<plugin name\>"]. - Configure the plugin through extraConfigLua: extraConfigLua = "require('my-plugin').setup({foo = "bar"})"; If a plugin isnt available from nixvim OR nixpkgs, then you should add it like so: { extraPlugins = [(pkgs.vimUtils.buildVimPlugin { name = "my-plugin"; src = pkgs.fetchFromGitHub { owner = "\<owner\>"; repo = "\<repo\>"; rev = "\<commit hash\>"; hash = "\<nix NAR hash\>"; }; })]; }

