47. ## Plugin Strategy
48. 
49. ### Available in NixVim (use `plugins.<name>.enable = true`)
50. - treesitter, treesitter-context
51. - lspconfig (with LSP servers configured natively)
52. - trouble
53. - lazydev
54. - rustaceanvim
55. - blink-cmp
56. - conform (conform-nvim)
57. - lint (nvim-lint)
58. - gitsigns
59. - diffview
60. - flash
61. - which-key
62. - bufferline
63. - lualine
64. - noice
65. - mini (pairs, surround)
66. - yanky
67. - yazi
68. - snacks
69. - todo-comments
70. - persistence
71. - overseer
72. - render-markdown
73. - obsidian
74. - illuminate (vim-illuminate / RRethy)
75. - inc-rename
76. - guess-indent
77. - ufo (nvim-ufo)
78. - catppuccin, tokyonight, nightfox, dracula (colorschemes)
79. - web-devicons
80. - lspkind
81. - copilot-lua
82. 
83. ### Available in nixpkgs vimPlugins (use `extraPlugins`)
84. - eldritch-theme/eldritch.nvim → `vimPlugins.eldritch-nvim` (or buildVimPlugin)
85. - git-blame.nvim → `vimPlugins.git-blame-nvim`
86. - numb.nvim → `vimPlugins.numb-nvim`
87. - quicker.nvim → `vimPlugins.quicker-nvim`
88. - nvim-highlight-colors → `vimPlugins.nvim-highlight-colors`
89. - friendly-snippets → `vimPlugins.friendly-snippets`
90. - helpview.nvim → `vimPlugins.helpview-nvim`
91. - markdown-toc (hedyhli) → check
92. - vim-kitty (fladson) → `vimPlugins.vim-kitty`
93. - vim-kitty-navigator → `vimPlugins.vim-kitty-navigator`
94. - kitty-scrollback → `vimPlugins.kitty-scrollback-nvim`
95. - clangd_extensions → `vimPlugins.clangd_extensions-nvim`
96. - onedark.nvim → `vimPlugins.onedark-nvim`
97. - nvim-scissors → likely available
98. - presenting.nvim → check
99. - hmts.nvim → check
100.
```

