```
100. 
101. ### Need `vimUtils.buildVimPlugin` (not in nixvim or nixpkgs)
102. - sidekick.nvim (folke/sidekick.nvim) — very new
103. - copilot-lsp (copilotlsp-nvim/copilot-lsp)
104. - blink-copilot (fang2hou/blink-copilot)
105. - tiny-inline-diagnostic.nvim (rachartier/tiny-inline-diagnostic.nvim)
106. - git-scripts.nvim (declancm/git-scripts.nvim)
107. - resolved.nvim (noamsto/resolved.nvim)
108. 
109. ### Not migrated (Mason-specific → replaced by Nix packages)
110. - mason.nvim, mason-lspconfig, mason-tool-installer
111. - → LSP servers + formatters + linters installed via `extraPackages`
112. - → LSP servers enabled via `plugins.lsp.servers.*`
113. 
114. ## Key Implementation Notes
115. 
116. 1. **LSP servers** are configured via `plugins.lsp.servers.<name>.enable = true` + `extraPackages` for the binaries. No Mason.
117. 2. **Formatters/Linters** (prettierd, stylua, eslint_d, black, etc.) go in `extraPackages`.
118. 3. **Eldritch theme** needs `extraPlugins` + `extraConfigLua` for setup.
119. 4. **Sidekick.nvim**, **copilot-lsp**, **blink-copilot** need `buildVimPlugin` with GitHub fetch.
120. 5. **Snippets** from `~/nvim/snippets/` need to be referenced via `config.snippetDir` or inlined.
121. 6. **WSL clipboard** logic stays as `extraConfigLua`.
122. 7. **Kitty** plugins are conditionally loaded — in nix we can use `mkIf` based on env variable checks.
123. 
124. ## LSP Servers to Enable
125. bash, json, go (gopls), lua-ls, basedpyright, yaml, docker-compose, dockerfile, cmake (neocmake), vtsls/typescript, terraform, clangd, zls (zig), emmet, fish, typos-lsp
126. 
127. ## Formatters/Linters in extraPackages
128. stylua, isort, black, prettierd (or prettier), markdownlint-cli2, eslint_d, kdlfmt, pylint, checkmake, yamllint, cmakelint, nixfmt
129. 
130. ## Todos
```

</details>


