```

In our snacks.nix, we have the `SnacksDim` highlight set via the VeryLazy autoCmd. But the original sets it in the config function which runs at plugin load. So in the original, the highlight is set immediately when snacks loads. In our nixvim config, it's set when VeryLazy fires. This might cause a brief flash of incorrect colors, but shouldn't prevent the dashboard from showing.

I'm noticing the timing difference here - the original applies the highlight during the config function execution, while our setup defers it to the VeryLazy event. This could be a minor visual issue but likely isn't the root cause of the dashboard not appearing.

